      "beast_baseline": "hey i think i found a leak in our order processing module. the memory usage just keeps climbing every time we execute a trade. i think it's something with how we're handling the order objects in this loop. can u look at this and tell me why it's leaking and how i can swap this out for smart pointers?\n\n```cpp\nvoid processOrders(std::vector<OrderData*>& orders) {\n    for (size_t i = 0; i < orders.size(); ++i) {\n        OrderData* currentOrder = new OrderData(orders[i].id, orders[i].price);\n        \n        if (currentOrder->isValid()) {\n            executeTrade(currentOrder);\n        }\n        // i think I'm missing something here?\n    }\n}\n```",
